The executive chooses to exercise the option or not according to which action maximizes his future payoff. If the after‐tax option return exceeds both the stock and bond returns, then leaving the option alive yields the greatest future payoff. If the return on either the stock or the bond exceeds the option return, then the executive’s best strategy is to exercise the option and invest the after‐tax profit in the asset with the greater return. The question of which return is greatest depends on the level of the future stock price. It also depends on the values of the other parameters. Let

